main event: A civilian observer reported seeing two unidentified flying objects in Lancaster, California on August 22, 1965.
interesting points: The larger object appeared round while the smaller object was shaped like a fly wing., The larger object changed from white to flashing lights as it maneuvered., The smaller object made a rapid maneuver estimated at over 3,000 mph., The larger object was visible for about 3 minutes while the smaller was visible for about 1 minute., The observer had significant flying experience with over 3,000 hours of flight time.
witness description: 11 years old, service engineer with General Electric, combined military and private flying time of over 3,000 hours
